        // so we take a look at the last character of the substring.
        // If the substring is empty, we return 0 because there is no chance of
        // finding anything.
        // The general algorithm is:
        // 1. Start a pointer at the first character of the string
        // 2. As long as the pointer doesn't reach the end of the string,
        //    we check if the character of the substring is the same
        // 3. If it is the same, we move the substring pointer
        //    If it is not the same, we go back to the start of the substring
        // 4. As long as the substring pointer is at the end of the substring,
        //    we can return the pointer-substring pointer
        // 5. If the substring pointer reaches the end of the string,
        //    we return the last pointer.
